  "source": "Theorem:\ngiven: k, m, n is \\set.theoretic.natural.number\nthen:\n. \\product:of{k}:and{\\sum:of{m}:and{n}} = \\sum:of{\\product:of{k}:and{m}}:and{\\product:of{k}:and{n}}\n. \\product:of{\\sum:of{k}:and{m}}:and{n} = \\sum:of{\\product:of{k}:and{n}}:and{\\product:of{m}:and{n}}\nDocumented:\n. description: \"Multiplication distributes over addition: for all $k, m, n \\in \\omega$, $k(m + n) = km + kn$ and $(k + m)n = kn + mn$.\"\nId: \"77b4c732-08a1-4e48-9ead-d13457f0c09b\"",
